# This file is based on the standard Visual Studio .gitignore template, 
# adapted for a C# API project.

## **Build Results**
# Ignore obj folders in all projects
obj/
**/obj/

# Exclude compiled output and temporary build files
**/[Bb]in/
**/[Oo]bj/
**/[Dd]ebug/
**/[Rr]elease/
**/[Tt]emp/
**/bin.bak/

# Project-specific intermediate files
**/*.user
**/*.suo
**/*.ncb
**/*.opensdf
**/*.sdf
**/*.cache
**/*.psess
**/*.vsp

## **Visual Studio Files**
# User-specific settings and solution files
*.vs/
*.[Ss]olution.v*
*.[Pp]roject.v*
*.log
*.plg
*.bak
*.trc
*.rsp

# IntelliSense and ReSharper
*.VC.db
*.bsc
*.sbr
*.res
*.pch
*.ipch
*.aps
*.res
*.suo

# NuGet cache and packages
**/packages/
# Exclude the project's 'packages' folder but keep 'nuget.config'
!**/packages.config
# Ignore NuGet generated folder in the solution root for restoration
.nuget/

## **Test Files**
# Results from running tests
**/TestResults/
**/*.trx

## **Rider/JetBrains IDE Files**
# Rider/ReSharper-specific files
.idea/
*.sln.DotSettings
*.sln.DotSettings.user

## **macOS Files**
# Files created by macOS
.DS_Store

## **Docker Files**
# Exclude generated output from Docker builds (if applicable)
**/docker-compose.vs.debug.g.yml
**/docker-compose.vs.release.g.yml
**/docker-compose.override.yml
# Include the standard override file if you want to commit it (remove the '!' if you don't)
!**/docker-compose.override.yml

## **Database Files**
# Local database files (e.g., SQLite, LocalDB)
*.mdf
*.ldf
*.sqlite
*.db

## **Dependency/Lock Files**
# Exclude files that can be regenerated, though often `project.assets.json` is useful for CI
**/project.assets.json
**/project.nuget.cache

## **Deployment Files**
# Web deploy/publish files
*.publish.xml